original: Ernulf, Torsten Gudmund, hov-rättsfiskal, Göteborg, f. 22/11/14 i Gbg av trafikchefen, civ :ing. Adolf Eriksson o. Carina Busck. G. 44 m. Marianne Cassel. — Stud:ex. v. Gbgs h. latin 33, jur. kand. i Lund 38. Tingstjg. i Hall. mell. doms. 38-41, tf. fiskal i Göta hovr. 42, ex. fiskal 44, tingssekr. i Askims m. fl. doms. sed. 46.
translated: Ernulf, Torsten Gudmund was a court prosecutor in Göteborg. He was born on November 22, 1914, in Gbg to the traffic manager, civil engineer Adolf Eriksson and Carina Busck. He married Marianne Cassel in 1944. He received his high school education at Gbgs h. latin in 1933 and his law degree at Lund in 1938. He served as a court clerk in Halland County Court from 1938 to 1941, acted as a temporary prosecutor in Göta Court of Appeal in 1942, became a court prosecutor in 1944, and finally worked as a court clerk in Askim and other district courts since 1946.
